AB  - The convertible bond is a hybrid security which, while retaining most of the characteristics of straight debt, offers, in addition, the upside potential associated with theunderlying common stock. As a quid pro quo for the upside potential the convertible bond is typically subordinated to other corporate debt and carries a lower coupon rate than would an otherwise equivalent straight bond.
